The paper addresses the problem of rank aggregation, which is a common problem in various fields such as information retrieval, machine learning, and data mining. The proposed method, Stochastic Rank Aggregation, involves incorporating uncertainty into rank aggregation and can be applied in both unsupervised and supervised scenarios. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.SI (social and information networks). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories as they are closely related to the proposed method.
